com.ampro.robinhood

Class Configuration

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.ampro.robinhood.Configuration

  • public class Configuration
extends java.lang.Object
    The Configuration stores authorization information about an instance of the RobinhoodApi.

    Many things (mostly ApiMethods) require a Configuration to function

      • hasToken

        public boolean hasToken()
        Whether or not an authToken exists. If an authToken does not exist than there is no current logged in user.
        Returns:
        true if an authToken exists

      • getToken

        public java.lang.String getToken()
        Method which gets the saved authorization token if the user is logged in. If one does not exist, it throws an error reminding the user to run the login functions first.
        Returns:
        the saved Token for the logged in user
        Throws:
        NotLoggedInException - if there is no stored Token. This must be populated by the setToken() method first

      • setAuthToken

        public void setAuthToken(java.lang.String token)
        Method which registers the authToken for the user into the Configuration Manager
        Parameters:
        token - verified Authorization Token for the user

        Throws:

      • getAccountUrl

        public java.lang.String getAccountUrl()
        Method returning the Account URL for the logged in user. This is created by appending the account number to a base URL. This is valid in most order requests.
        Returns:
        the account URL
        Throws:
        NotLoggedInException - If the Configuration is not logged in

      • getDefault

        public static Configuration getDefault()
        Returns:
        The default Configuration (i.e. with no account data)

      • getRatelimit

        public static long getRatelimit()
        Returns:
        the current ratelimit. By default, this is 500 milliseconds (.5 seconds)
